snippet.title: Conjoined Twin Sisters Tell Their Story: ‘Being By Her … It’s So Calming' | Megyn Kelly TODAY
snippet.description:
Emily and James Stark gave birth to conjoined twins Lexi and Sydney Stark on March 9, 2001. The family joins Megyn Kelly TODAY with the story of the twins’ risky separation surgery, as well as their lives now. The girls talk how they still nap in what they call the “conjoined twin position,” and call being near each other “calming.”
